The paper deals with the problem of embedding a subset of $\mathbb{R}^N$ into another subset of $\delta\mathbb{Z}^M$ using a quantized random linear mapping. This problem is related to compressed sensing, machine learning, and signal processing, which are all covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, and cs.NA. Additionally, the paper discusses the Gaussian mean width of the subset, which is a concept from convex geometry and optimization, making cs.DS a likely sub-category as well.
